{
  "texts": [
    "Large Language Models (LLMs) are potential tools for analyzing item texts.",
    "Many studies have used LLMs such as ChatGPT in the education scenario, including generalizing questions and hints (Bohacek, 2023), playing as a learning tutor chatbot (Yadav et al., 2023), and even scoring essays (Caines et al., 2023).",
    "With item texts, it is possible to use LLMs to estimate item characteristics and cluster items for different skills, which can save expert annotations and accelerate largescale applications in the future.",
    "However, in this study, we focus on modeling student states using facial features, and thus, the extension of using LLMs in student performance prediction is out of scope.",
    "Unlike facial-video-based methods, log-based methods typically do not assume that the student's affective state influences the response."
  ]
}